name: ontimize-boot
description: Ontimize Boot uses Spring Boot technology to further simplify the development of a service or         microservice based server, using the API REST communication system.

name: microservice-wallet-system
description: This is the backend system for the E-Wallet application, built with a microservices architecture to ensure scalability and maintainability. The system is composed of several microservices, including the Auth microservice for authentication and token management, the Wallet microservice for managing wallet operations and in-app transactions etc.

name: Credit-Management-System-With-Spring-Cloud
description: Microservices in Spring Boot including microservices for managing client data, credit evaluation, and card issuance. Secure access with JWT tokens and Keycloak. Utilizes both synchronous and asynchronous communication patterns with OpenFeign and RabbitMQ. Docker is used for containerization.

name: reservation-system
description: A reservation system built using nestjs, following microservice architecture.

name: Task-Management-Microservice
description: This project is a Task Management System designed to streamline task creation, assignment, and tracking across teams. It allows admins to create and assign tasks to registered users, track progress, and review task submissions. The system is built using a microservices architecture, ensuring scalability and modularity.

name: numer
description: A microservices backend to support an invoice management system.

name: Gym-Management-System
description: A modular solution for managing gym operations with microservices for attendance, members, and trainers, plus a React-based frontend.

name: Sound-Sphere-Auth-Microservice
description: The SoundSphere Auth microservice is responsible for managing authentication and authorization within the eCommerce system. It handles user registration, login, and token management, ensuring secure access to the platform's resources.

name: Microservices-spring-boot
description: This project uses a  Microservice Architecture designed to demonstrate a scalable, distributed system that is easy to manage, maintain, and extend. The microservices interact seamlessly with each other, leveraging modern cloud-native technologies and DevOps practices to ensure high availability and optimal performance

name: E-commerce-Microservices-Application
description: This project is an e-commerce platform built using a microservices architecture to ensure scalability, flexibility, and resilience. The system is composed of multiple independent services that interact through Kafka, a distributed message broker, to handle communication between services efficiently.

name: Springboot-Microservices-ReactJS-MySQL
description: A scalable system using Spring Boot, ReactJS, and MySQL. Features include an API Gateway for routing, Department, Employee, and Organization Services for data management, React Frontend for UI, Eureka for service discovery, Spring Config Server for centralized config, and Zipkin for tracing.

name: ERP-System
description: Development of an ERP system using microservices architecture to integrate customer services, products, inventory, shipping and payments. Implementation of REST APIs for communication between modules, ensuring data verification and order processing. Use of RabbitMQ for messaging and event exchange between services,
